message: This year has seen the tragic loss of many transgender people around the world due to senseless transphobic violence, the majority of whom are black & Latinx transgender women.   More needs to be done to protect the life & dignity of this community.      TransDayOfRemembrance CEDAWPeople’sTribunal  · 21 Nov 2020  CEDAW General Recommendation No.35 urges states to take an intersectional approach when combatting  VAW.  In particular, it recognises that trans women are uniquely vulnerable to violence due to their intersecting identities.   TransDayOfRemembrance   http://CEDAWPT.com
